    {
      "type": "volkovlabs-form-panel",
      "id": 54,
      "title": "Run a bufferbloat test on an IP",
      "description": "Enter an IP (or hostname), pick a direction, and click run. The prober saturates the link in that direction while pinging the IP. The run takes ~10–25s: the 'Test status' panel shows 'Running…', then the idle-vs-loaded RTT and grade appear in the 'Last on-demand test' panels and as a timeline annotation. Proxied server-side through Grafana to the prober (no prober port exposed). Generates real traffic; rate-limited.",
